9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 644, L.D. 997, “An Act to Allow
10 Residential Use Development in Commercial Districts”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 30-A MRSA §4364-C, sub-§3, as amended by PL 2023, c. 536, §1, is
14 repealed.
15 Sec. 2. 30-A MRSA §4364-D is enacted to read:
16 §4364-D. Residential units in areas zoned for commercial use
17 A municipality shall allow residential units within buildings located in an area zoned
18 for commercial use, including, but not limited to, buildings that are vacant or partially
19 vacant retail property, except when a municipality determines that flooding or other natural
20 hazards in the zone makes a building located in an area zoned for commercial use unfit for
21 residential use. For purposes of this section, "commercial use" means the use of lands,
22 buildings or structures the intent or result of which is the production of income from the
23 buying or selling of goods or services. "Commercial use" does not include a home-based
24 business, the rental of a single dwelling unit on a single lot or incidental sales of goods or
25 services as may be allowed by permit or standard.
26 1. Allowable limitation on residential units in areas zoned for commercial use.
27 An ordinance adopted by a municipality that regulates the establishment of residential units
28 in an area zoned for commercial use may establish standards that limit the number of
29 residential units in a commercial development.
30 2. Allowable requirement for commercial use on ground floor. An ordinance
31 adopted by a municipality that regulates the establishment of residential units in an area
32 zoned for commercial use may require the ground floor of a building containing residential
33 units to be restricted for commercial use.
34 3. Allowable siting and design requirements for residential units in areas zoned
35 for commercial use. A municipality may adopt an ordinance regulating the siting and
Page 1 - 132LR1162(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 644, L.D. 997
316 design of a residential or mixed-use development established in an area zoned for
327 commercial use as long as the ordinance, alone or in combination with other siting and
338 design ordinances, does not discourage the development through unreasonable costs or
349 delays.
5 4. Prohibited limitations on residential development. An ordinance adopted by a
6 municipality that regulates residential development in an area zoned for commercial use
7 may not contain restrictions or limitations more stringent than the restrictions or limitations
8 contained in section 4364, 4364-A or 4364-B.
9 5. Health and safety requirements. This section is not intended to reduce or change
10 health or safety requirements applicable to residential units located in a municipality.
11 6. Rulemaking. The state agency responsible for administering the Housing
12 Opportunity Program established in Title 5, section 13056-J may adopt rules to administer
13 and enforce this section. Rules adopted pursuant to this subsection are routine technical
14 rules as defined in Title 5, chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.
15 7. Implementation. A municipality must comply with the requirements of this section
16 beginning July 1, 2027.'
17 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
18 number to read consecutively.
19 SUMMARY
2200 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill. The
2211 amendment requires a municipality to allow residential units within buildings in an area
2222 zoned for commercial use. The amendment allows the state agency responsible for the
2233 Housing Opportunity Program to adopt rules to administer and enforce this legislation. A
2244 municipality must comply with the requirements of this legislation beginning July 1, 2027.
